<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
LIBYA; 
</P>
<P>
KADAFI WARNS EAST BLOC ON DEMOCRACY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Leader Moammar Kadafi said capitalism and Western-style democracy could ravage 
reformist Eastern Europe. 
</P>
<P>
He told a news conference in Tripoli that if Eastern Europe adopts a "Western 
European system with its multi-parties and capitalism, I warn you of 
unemployment and beggars, of inflation, crises and, in the end, war." In a 
surprise departure, the rabidly anti-Israeli Kadafi accused the West of 
plotting to rid the world of Jews by placing them in "Palestine, the tomb of 
Jews, the mass oven for Jews." The Jews, he conceded, "are oppressed in the 
world," adding that Libya "would welcome them back." 
</P>
