<P>
OIL REFINERY LEAK BEING INVESTIGATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Officials in New Jersey said they have opened a criminal investigation into the 
underwater oil leak from Exxon's Bayway refinery in Linden. 
</P>
<P>
Subpoenas have been served on six Exxon employees, a spokesman for the New 
Jersey attorney general said. More than half a million gallons of heating oil 
spilled into the Arthur Kill waterway between New Jersey and New York City last 
week after a pipeline was struck by an unidentified vessel. The Coast Guard 
said it will use oil-catching filter fences to protect marshlands on Staten 
Island and the New Jersey coast. 
</P>
</TEXT>
