<P>
EXPENSE ACCOUNTS QUESTIONED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nine Fresno County Elections division employees are suspected of overbilling 
the county more than $1,600 in questionable travel expenses, according to a 
report by the county auditor. "The questionable expenses include excessive 
mileage claimed, meals claimed for what appears to be earlier-than-necessary 
departure or later-than-necessary return times and unnecessary car rentals," 
the report said. The report said that $1,272 of the questionable expenses were 
paid to Elections Manager Norma Logan, who has been on medical leave. 
</P>
