<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPRINKLER SYSTEMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I certainly agree with your editorial (Dec. 24) about mandatory sprinkler 
systems for homes, but before this can be done, the installation cost must be 
reduced and the insurance companies made to provide the reduced rate you seem 
to think exists. An estimate I received recently for a new home put the price 
of sprinklers over twice what you estimated. I have yet to find an insurance 
company that gives a reduced rate for sprinklers in a home. 
</P>
<P>
BRUCE M. STARK 
</P>
<P>
Seal Beach 
</P>
