<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA COLLEGE RALLIES TO DEFEAT OCCIDENTAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Southern California College won the Occidental College men's basketball 
tournament Saturday night by defeating the host team, 72-58. 
</P>
<P>
Trailing at halftime, 23-19, SCC scored the first six points of the second half 
to pull away. 
</P>
<P>
Center Jeff Bickmore had eight rebounds and led SCC (8-5) down the stretch, as 
17 of his 21 points came in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
"We weren't playing within our offense in the first half," said Bickmore, a 
6-foot-7, 210-pound junior from Santa Ana. "We made that adjustment in the 
second half, and I got the shots I wanted." 
</P>
<P>
Center Chris Anderson led Occidental (5-8) with 20 points. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference men's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
Christ College Irvine 91, Fontbonne 85 -- Kevin Kurz had 24 points and Mike 
Oden 22 to lead Christ College Irvine. Aaron Clasen had 13 points and Jamie 
McShan 10 for Christ College Irvine (8-10). 
</P>
<P>
In women's nonconference basketball: 
</P>
<P>
Chapman College 90, North Carolina Greensboro 55 -- Leading 19-15 four minutes 
into the game, host Chapman College went on a 17-0 run over the next four 
minutes en route to a 46-29 halftime lead and was never challenged. Forward 
Bethel Trice had 26 points to lead Chapman (11-3). Teammate Ruth Akahoshi added 
23, including 18 points on 6-for-12 shooting from three-point range. Greensboro 
(7-2) was led by forward Karen Jordan's 14 points. Center Jennifer Uecke had 16 
points and 13 rebounds for Chapman. 
</P>
<P>
At the UC Irvine swimming invitational: 
</P>
<P>
UC Irvine's Jeff Klatt won the 200-yard individual medley and teammate Dave 
Pohlmann won the the 500-yard freestyle in the first day of the swim meet at 
Irvine's Heritage Park. 
</P>
<P>
Klatt had a time of 1 minute, 59.48 seconds and Pohlmann had a time of 4:43.95. 
The Irvine men also won the 400 medley relay in 3:34.67. 
</P>
<P>
In the women's division, Irvine's Danielle Pajer (1:10.43) was second in the 
100 breaststroke behind Cal State Long Beach's Kelley Evans (1:09.62), and 
Irvine's Debbie Babashoff (5:13.95) was second in the 500 freestyle behind Long 
Beach's Lynnet Kosmala (5:11.68). Irvine was third in the 800 freestyle relay 
with a time of 8:13.66. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference wrestling: 
</P>
<P>
Northern Iowa 20, Cal State Fullerton 15 -- Northern Iowa, the 10th-ranked team 
in the nation, defeated host Fullerton by winning five of the 10 matches and 
earning a tie in a sixth match. Fullerton is 3-5 and Northern Iowa 7-1. David 
Jones defeated Greg Berg, 15-8, in the heavyweight division for Fullerton. 
</P>
</TEXT>
