<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL NEWS: CHILDREN TOO YOUNG FOR SCHOOL LAST YEAR CAN GET AN EARLY START 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Gabriel School District will offer Early Start Kindergarten during the 
spring semester beginning Feb. 5. 
</P>
<P>
The program gives children who missed the cutoff date to start school last year 
an opportunity to attend school prior to enrolling for a full year in 
kindergarten. 
</P>
<P>
The curriculum focuses on teaching skills children will need to succeed in 
kindergarten. Classes run from 11:45 a.m. to 3:05 p.m., and school lunches are 
available. 
</P>
<P>
All children who turn 5 by April 1 are eligible. Classes will be held at 
McKinley School, 1425 Manley Drive, San Gabriel. 
</P>
