<HEADLINE>
<P>
REPUBLICANS AND ABORTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gov. Deukmejian demonstrated that he is truly a lame-duck leader. 
</P>
<P>
By recommending that Republican anti-choice candidates stick to their 
traditional positions on reproductive freedom issues, he has relegated the 
Republican Party to permanent minority status in California and in the state 
Legislature. 
</P>
<P>
A 1989 Harris poll showed that 68% of all registered Republicans would oppose a 
constitutional amendment banning access to abortion. GOP anti-choice candidates 
will continue to lose if they don't recognize this important fact. 
</P>
<P>
The governor is right, abortion is a moral issue, but the Webster vs. 
Reproductive Health Services Supreme Court decision guaranteed that it is also 
a political issue. If Republicans heed Deukmejian's advice, there is no future 
for our party in leading California. 
</P>
<P>
JULIA A. JUSTUS 
</P>
<P>
La Verne 
</P>
</TEXT>
