<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAVING CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The commentary "We Could Give the Gift of Life This Christmas" (Op-Ed Page, 
Dec. 24) outraged and dismayed me. To allow 40,000 children to needlessly die 
daily is literally beyond belief! But even if we do not respond to this 
unnecessary condition on humane grounds, it well behooves us to look at it from 
a selfish stance. 
</P>
<P>
High child death rates mean high birth rates; the poverty which promotes these 
death rates forces millions to over-exploit their surroundings just to survive; 
poverty provokes instability and violence; poverty perpetuates itself. It sows 
the seeds of social problems. We feel the results of all of this in our own 
country. So for either selfish or unselfish reasons, we must realize that 
children are indeed dying for us to learn this. 
</P>
<P>
BARBARA URSCHEL 
</P>
<P>
Mission Viejo 
</P>
</TEXT>
