<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE MOVIE CHART: FILMS GOING INTO PRODUCTION: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By David Pecchia 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Almost an Angel (Ironbark). Shooting in L.A. The "Crocodile" man Paul Hogan 
stars, again with his favorite onscreen (and offscreen) leading lady, Linda 
Kozlowski, and it's produced and directed by "Croc II's" John Cornell. 
</P>
<P>
All we know is that it's a comedy and that on this trip Hogan doesn't play an 
endearing reptile slayer from Australia's Outback. Executive 
producer/screenwriter Hogan. Also stars Elias Koteas. Distributor Paramount. 
Winter release. 
</P>
<P>
Rosencrantz and Guildenstern Are Dead (Michael Brandman Prod.). Shooting in 
Yugoslavia. It's based on Tom Stoppard's existential comedy (which Stoppard 
adapts and directs). In Shakespeare's "Hamlet," R&amp;G were plotting to commit 
murder -- here, they end up on the wrong end of one. Executive producers Tom 
Rizzo and Louise Stephens. Producers Michael Brandman and Emanuel Azenberg. 
Stars Richard Dreyfuss, Gary Oldman, Tim Roth, Ian Richardson, Joanna Miles and 
Donald Sumpter. Distributor Cinecom. David Pecchia 
</P>
</TEXT>
