<HEADLINE>
<P>
'TOUGH LOVE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Obviously, P. Lucius Sladek Jr. and Frank L. Burke, whose Dec. 24 letters 
blasted Bill Cosby, have had radically different experiences with dishonest 
and/or addicted children than I have had. 
</P>
<P>
Having seen "open-minded and understanding" parents give unlimited support and 
love in a frustrating and fruitless effort to help offspring salvage their 
lives, I feel I can comment knowledgeably on the subject. 
</P>
<P>
My well-meaning parents' never-ending efforts to help those who "strayed from 
the mold" have drained and disrupted four generations; one after another, the 
children and grandchildren were affected by the tumultuous household. 
</P>
<P>
It is not easy to use the "tough love" method, but the survival of a whole 
family must be considered. 
</P>
<P>
M. ATTEBERRY 
</P>
<P>
Torrance 
</P>
</TEXT>
