<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAMPANELLA'S CONDITION IS IMPROVED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Dodger catcher Roy Campanella, who was admitted to Northridge Hospital 
Medical Center Dec. 30 with pneumonia and diabetes complications, is showing 
gradual improvement, a nursing supervisor said Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
Campanella, 68, a Hall of Famer who is a member of the club's community 
relations services department, is listed in serious but stable condition. His 
condition was listed as serious Friday. 
</P>
<P>
He is still in the intensive care unit and is breathing with the assistance of 
a respiratory machine, but he is slowly being taken off the machine, the 
nursing supervisor said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
